   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1816-12_page02.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <name type="place" ref="Id_where"/>Edgeworths Town
                  <date when="1816-12-28"/><choice><orig>Dec<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></orig><reg>December</reg></choice>. 28<hi rend="superscript">h</hi> 1816</dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Miles</persName> - This</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>day we received <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Miles's</persName><lb/>
               answer to my <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">father's</persName> letter<lb/>
               written I think in your<lb/>
               handwriting - Why did not<lb/>
               you tell me that you had<lb/>
               been ill after your <choice><orig>confine<lb/>
               ment</orig><reg>confinement</reg></choice>? - You said not one<lb/>
               word of this in your very<lb/>
               kind letter to me and<lb/>
               this led me into doing<lb/>
               what was very <choice><orig>inconsider<lb/>
               =ate</orig><reg>inconsiderate</reg></choice> and what if I had<lb/>
               known the circumstances<lb/>
               would have been indeed<lb/>
               most unfeeling &amp; brutal.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1816-12_page03.jpg"/>
               Had I had the least idea that<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Miles</persName> had been at all<lb/>
               dangerously ill or that<lb/>
               you had been confined to<lb/>
               your room it would have<lb/>
               been utterly impossible that<lb/>
               I could have written to ask<lb/>
               you to chuse shawls for me<lb/>
               and I have now only to<lb/>
               entreat you to excuse me<lb/>
               and earnestly to beg that<lb/>
               you will <hi rend="underline">forget</hi> the two<lb/>
               letters I have written to you<lb/>
               about the shawls or at least<lb/>
               never think of them till <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.<lb/>
               Miles</persName> is fairly <hi rend="underline">on afoot</hi> again<lb/>
               and till you have been<lb/>
               out several times and<lb/>
               feel free from all remains<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1816-12_page04.jpg"/>
               both of illness and anxiety<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               I am sincerely sorry<lb/>
               my good friend <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Miles</persName><lb/>
               has suffered so much and<lb/>
               I beg you will remember<lb/>
               me to him in the kindest<lb/>
               manner - I thank him<lb/>
               for thinking of me and<lb/>
               my books when he was<lb/>
               suffering - My <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">father</persName><lb/>
               is very much of obliged to<lb/>
               him - He will answer<lb/>
               for himself - But I was<lb/>
               determined to write <choice><orig>im<lb/>
               =mediately</orig><reg>immediately</reg></choice> myself to<lb/>
               represent that I really<lb/>
               am not a brute<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               I am my dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Miles</persName><lb/>
               yours very sincerely<lb/>
               Maria Edgeworth<lb/>
            </closer>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <addrLine><persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Miles</persName></addrLine><lb/>
                  <addrLine><placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#West-End-Hampstead_ENK">West End</placeName></addrLine><lb/>
                  <addrLine><placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName></addrLine><lb/>
                </address>
            </closer>
